<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2879] TMemoryBuffer: using lua string in wrong way</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2879</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1. &lt;br/&gt;
local val = string.sub(self.buffer, self.rPos, len)&lt;br/&gt;
The call string.sub(s,i,j) extracts a piece of the string s, &lt;br/&gt;
from the i-th to the j-th character inclusive. &lt;br/&gt;
In Lua, the first character of a string has index 1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.&lt;br/&gt;
self.buffer = self.buffer + buf&lt;br/&gt;
self.wPos = self.wPos + buf&lt;br/&gt;
.. is the string concatenation operator in Lua, not +.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
